                  <div>
                     <p class="css-inh89d">The Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation (BMC) has successfully vaccinated approximately 25,000 out of the total 165,000 stray dogs in Mumbai as part of its ongoing mass anti-rabies vaccination initiative since September 2023. According to reports, the civic body aims to achieve a minimum of 70 percent vaccination coverage for the city's stray dogs by March 2024.</p>
                     <p class="css-inh89d">This initiative forms an integral component of the Mumbai Rabies Elimination Project, a comprehensive campaign for mass anti-rabies vaccination targeting stray dogs. Collaborating with animal welfare organizations like the Janice Smith Animal Welfare Trust, Youth Organization in Defense of Animals, Universal Animal Welfare Society, and Utkarsh Global Foundation, the BMC is actively working towards this ambitious goal.</p>
                     <p class="css-inh89d">Dr. Kalimpasha Pathan, the General Manager of the Veterinary Department and Deonar Abattoir, emphasized that the primary objective of this initiative is to curb the spread of rabies‚Äîa fatal viral disease with severe implications for both human and animal populations. </p>
                     <p class="css-inh89d">Rabies is preventable, transmitted through the saliva of infected animals, mainly via bites. Stray dogs, often susceptible due to a lack of proper care and vaccination, serve as significant carriers of rabies in urban areas.</p>
                     <p class="css-inh89d">The mass vaccination drive involves a team of trained professionals equipped with safe and effective rabies vaccines. These teams strategically traverse the city, ensuring accessibility and comprehensive coverage of stray dog populations in various neighbourhoods.</p>
                     <p class="css-inh89d">BMC is urging all residents to actively support this crucial public health initiative. Residents can contribute by ensuring their pets are up-to-date on rabies vaccination, reporting any stray dogs to designated authorities for vaccination, and allowing the participating organizations to carry out their work effectively in the city, as stated by the civic body.</p>
